0; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-botto=
m-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">SEC=
=E2=80=99s rules</a> require brokerage firms to preserve =E2=80=9Coriginals=
 of all communications received and copies of all communications sent =E2=
=80=A6 (including inter-office memoranda and communications) relating to it=
s business as such.=E2=80=9D And the SEC has been methodically working thro=
ugh every big investment bank and brokerage, examining their records, sampl=
ing some employees=E2=80=99 personal phones, discovering that every single =
bank with no exceptions whatsoever has employees who talk about work on tex=
ts or WhatsApp, and fining those banks millions of dollars for recordkeepin=
g failures.=C2=A0We have <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com=
