<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The SEC might plausibly come to a broker in 19=
48 and say =E2=80=9Cshow me all of your internal communications for the las=
t two years,=E2=80=9D and he (he) might hand the SEC, like, 30 memos, and t=
he SEC might say =E2=80=9Cah right that=E2=80=99s a reasonable number of me=
mos=E2=80=9D and then go read them.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One thing that has happened in the intervening=
 74 years is that written communication has become much much much much much=
 much much easier and more casual. I used to work on a desk at Goldman Sach=
s Group Inc., where the default method of communication with someone who sa=
t <em>two</em> seats away from you was instant messaging.=C2=A0There were s=
ome mornings when I sent more than 100 inter-office memoranda, though like =
20 of them would be =E2=80=9Clol=E2=80=9D or =E2=80=9Cfml.=E2=80=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But you can certainly <a href=3D"https://link.=
mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32335917.262411/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZX=
JnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDItMDIvdGhlLXNlYy13YW50cy10by1zZWUtb=
