none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bo=
rder-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  see where the SEC is c=
oming from</a>. For one thing, every single firm is uniformly guilty, so it=
 is easy to extract large fines from all of them; the SEC is not exactly a =
profit-maximizing entity but it is not entirely not that either. For anothe=
r thing, this enforcement push is very helpful for=C2=A0<em>other=C2=A0</em=
>enforcement pushes: The upshot of these cases is not only that investment =
banks and brokers pay big fines now, but also that they will do a more cons=
cientious job of discussing business only on monitored channels, so that wh=
en the=C2=A0<em>next=C2=A0</em>scandal happens the SEC will have an easier =
time gathering evidence.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">You could think up weirder hypotheticals about=
 what is and isn=E2=80=99t allowed:</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: disc; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=
=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">If you want to arrange a golf outing w=
ith a client, can you text her from your personal phone saying =E2=80=9Clet=
=E2=80=99s play golf tomorrow=E2=80=9D? On the one hand, that is not a comm=
unication about a deal. On the other hand, if you regularly discuss deals o=
n the golf course, it=E2=80=99s kind of about a deal.=C2=A0</li>=09<li styl=
e=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Can you text a client restaurant recommendations,=
 or memes, from your personal phone? Ask her how her family is doing? You=
=E2=80=99re not discussing deals, but of course the entire client relations=
hip is part of the process of=C2=A0<em>getting=C2=A0</em>deals; you are not=
 chatting with her out of pure friendship. It=E2=80=99s kind of a business =
communication.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">If you meet with a =
client in a conference room, write a draft plan for a deal on a legal pad, =
and then hand her the legal pad, is that a formal written communication tha=
t should have been made on official channels? What if you write it on a whi=
teboard? What if you meet with her in a restaurant and write it on a napkin=
? Will the SEC fine your bank, saying =E2=80=9Ca managing director once com=
municated with a client about a deal on a napkin, instead of on official ch=
annels=E2=80=9D? That would be a fun complaint.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-=
bottom: 5px;">Can you send clients=C2=A0<em>LinkedIn=C2=A0</em>messages abo=
ut business? On the one hand, I guess your firm doesn=E2=80=99t monitor and=
 archive LinkedIn messages. On the other hand, man, it is LinkedIn. There i=
s no form of communication on earth that=C2=A0<em>feels=C2=A0</em>more form=
al and official than LinkedIn, or more earnest and businesslike. It just se=
ems impossible to do crimes on LinkedIn.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D=
"#footnote-2" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bo=
rder-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: =
none !important; background-color: transparent !important; display: inline-=
block;">
<span>[2]</span>
</a>
</li>
</ul>
