<tr>
<td class=3D"body-header-container" style=3D"border-collapse: collapse; mso=
-table-lspace: 0pt; mso-table-rspace: 0pt;">
<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">ESG</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">For a while, environmental, social and governa=
nce investing was a hot marketing=C2=A0tool in the investing world: If you =
did ESG, some people would say =E2=80=9Coh ESG I like that,=E2=80=9D and no=
body would say =E2=80=9Coh ESG I don=E2=80=99t like that,=E2=80=9D so you w=
ould gain customers and not lose any. And because ESG was a fairly fuzzy co=
ncept, you could =E2=80=9Cdo ESG=E2=80=9D without too much effort: If you j=
ust bought the stocks that you wanted to buy, but before you clicked =E2=80=
=9Cbuy=E2=80=9D you spent=C2=A0five seconds asking yourself =E2=80=9Cdo I f=
eel like this company is pretty green,=E2=80=9D that was probably ESG enoug=
h to slap the label on your fund.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Not anymore! Now lots of people =E2=80=94=C2=
=A0primarily US Republican politicians=C2=A0=E2=80=94=C2=A0say =E2=80=9Coh =
ESG I hate that,=E2=80=9D so the ESG label will alienate lots of customers.=
 And lots of other people still say =E2=80=9Coh ESG I like that,=E2=80=9D b=
ut their standards have gone up: Now, if you advertise that you are ESG, yo=
u have to take it seriously. Now, if you advertise that you are ESG but peo=
ple do not trust your ESG evaluations,=C2=A0you can get in trouble =E2=80=
=94=C2=A0with customers and possibly <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomberg=
business.com/click/32335917.262411/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGlu=
aW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDUtMjMvdGhlLXNlYy1nb2VzLWFmdGVyLWdyZWVud2FzaGluZz9=
jbXBpZD1CQkQwODA4MjNfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bm=
V3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMzA4MDgmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07cee=
f4b8524a319a23cB07cbd6ba" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" ta=
rget=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; =
border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style=
: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  with regulators</a> =E2=80=94=C2=A0for =
=E2=80=9Cgreenwashing.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">There are, I suspect, a number of investment m=
anagers and other related professionals who got pretty into ESG when the ge=
tting was good, and now wish they had never heard of it. The <a href=3D"htt=
ps://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32335917.262411/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cu=
ZnQuY29tL2NvbnRlbnQvOTQyNjkzN2UtMjhkMy00ODQ2LTg0NDAtYzMwNTgzNTI0ZDRj/607f07=
ceef4b8524a319a23cB8aa828e7" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope"=
 target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !importan=
t; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-st=
yle: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> Financial Times reports</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">S&amp;P Global has stopped handing out scores =
to corporate borrowers on ESG criteria, at a time of rising questions about=
 their utility and political attacks on such metrics.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The debt rating agency has since 2021 publishe=
d scores from one to five for a company=E2=80=99s exposure to each element =
of environmental, social and governance risks.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Payments company Visa, for example, had receiv=
ed a two for =E2=80=9CE=E2=80=9D and =E2=80=9CS=E2=80=9D and a three for =
=E2=80=9CG=E2=80=9D. FirstEnergy, an Ohio utility that has been charged wit=
h corruption, received a four score for =E2=80=9CG=E2=80=9D, S&amp;P=E2=80=
=99s second-lowest grade.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Late last week S&amp;P reversed course, saying=
 that only text, not numerical scores, would comprise analysis of a company=
=E2=80=99s ESG matters.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CWe have determined that the dedicated=
 analytical narrative paragraphs in our credit rating reports are most effe=
ctive at providing detail and transparency on ESG credit factors material t=
o our rating analysis,=E2=80=9D the rating agency said.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Very reasonable. My favorite part of the story=
, though, is this guy:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Tom Lyon, a professor at University of Michiga=
n=E2=80=99s business school who has studied ESG ratings, said S&amp;P move =
was =E2=80=9Cjust the latest example of a company crumpling in the face of =
these Republican attacks=E2=80=9D.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Their attacks have also overshadowed real conc=
erns about ESG ratings sold by S&amp;P and other financial firms, Lyon said=
. =E2=80=9CThey are not that reliable and they disagree.=E2=80=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CI think they stopped doing ESG rating=
s for Reason X, and I disapprove; they should have stopped doing ESG rating=
s for Reason Y.=E2=80=9D Yes, right, all the more reason to stop!</p>
