<tr>
<td class=3D"body-header-container" style=3D"border-collapse: collapse; mso=
-table-lspace: 0pt; mso-table-rspace: 0pt;">
<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Goldman in Russia</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I guess that if you are a global investment ba=
nk with a presence in Russia, you have some assets in Russia, and you have =
some liabilities in Russia. You own Russian stocks and bonds and what have =
you, on the one hand, and on the other hand you have some derivatives trade=
s where you owe Russian clients money. When Russia invaded Ukraine, you qui=
ckly had to stop dealing with Russia, for sanctions and reputational reason=
s. This meant, on the one hand, that you couldn=E2=80=99t really=C2=A0<em>u=
se=C2=A0</em>your Russian assets: Perhaps you could quickly dump some of yo=
ur Russian stocks and bonds, but private stakes and anything illiquid are k=
ind of just out of reach, sitting in Russia but unavailable to you. And on =
the other hand, you can=E2=80=99t really pay your Russian liabilities: Wiri=
ng money to a sanctioned Russian bank to settle a derivatives trade, for in=
stance, is going to make your compliance officer nervous.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Probably the assets and liabilities partially =
offset each other, though, and an approximate solution is to abandon everyt=
hing, tell your Russian creditors =E2=80=9Clook we have some Russian assets=
 we=E2=80=99re not using but <em>we=C2=A0</em>can=E2=80=99t give them to yo=
u,=E2=80=9D and let the Russians=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomber=
gbusiness.com/click/32335917.262411/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZnQuY29tL2NvbnRlbnQvYjQ=
4ODY0NjMtYzljZC00NTY4LThmMzQtNDExOTc5Y2QzZGNh/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB796e=
3dfe" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" styl=
e=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width:=
 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-=
color: #ccc;">sort it out</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A Russian court has frozen about $36mn worth o=
f Goldman Sachs=E2=80=99 assets in the country after state-owned bank Otkri=
tie, which is under western sanctions, filed a lawsuit against the US bank.=
</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Otkritie accused Goldman of refusing to fulfil=
 Rbs615mn ($6.4mn) of debt obligations under derivatives agreements between=
 the two banks. According to court documents published earlier this month, =
Goldman had pointed to the sanctions imposed against the Russian bank by th=
e US and other western countries for not being able to settle the debt.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Otkritie claimed that Goldman Sachs wanted to =
leave Russia, which would make debt collection impossible, and requested th=
at the court temporarily seize the US bank=E2=80=99s assets until the case =
was resolved. Goldman on Monday declined to comment on the court=E2=80=99s =
decision.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The temporarily frozen assets include a 5 per =
cent stake worth $27mn, based on the latest share price, in Russia=E2=80=99=
s largest children=E2=80=99s goods retailer Detsky Mir, which means =E2=80=
=9Cchildren=E2=80=99s world=E2=80=9D. Goldman was a bookrunner for the comp=
any=E2=80=99s listing in Moscow in 2017.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The document showed that the court ordered the=
 temporary seizure of smaller stakes in other Russian companies owned by a =
Luxembourg-registered Goldman Sachs III SICAV fund.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">These assets include shares in leading Russian=
 lenders Sberbank and VTB, which now owns Otkritie, as well as Gazprom, Luk=
oil, Russia=E2=80=99s largest airline Aeroflot =E2=80=94 all under sanction=
s from the west =E2=80=94 and one of the country=E2=80=99s top retailers, M=
agnit.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Goldman fund had written down the price of=
 these assets to zero, according to its 2022 annual report. However, based =
on the companies=E2=80=99 latest share price, their market value exceeds $9=
.3mn.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Yeah I mean those assets were frozen before, t=
oo. So were those liabilities. There=E2=80=99s a trade to be done, as long =
as Goldman doesn=E2=80=99t do it.</p>
